column5: Our controlled hunt didn't go too well this year, but my back yard cam caught a few. The camera is 100yrds from the house, BUT unfortunately theres no hunting permitted, FIGURES! The last photo is my bonus. Thought I'll share some photos since I haven't posted in a while. Enjoy!              Sorry about the quality, rain on the lens.            Didn't expect this one.    This was a bonus photo from my ladder stand before the hunt.
Nice cam shot Dan. Good to hear from you.
Those are some really nice shots. Can you not bow hunt in that area?
awesome shots man !!!! lots of critters around your place for sure...!!!
Is that a 3-legged deer in the third pic?
Nice pics man.  I'm going to have a "back yard cam" in a few weeks.  But I CAN hunt there

"Those are some really nice shots. Can you not bow hunt in that area? "  That was what I was thinking as well.  I love game cam's , it's amazing what's running around at night that people don't know about!!  Thanks for the pics!

He's in Schomberg....  Areas in York Region have the strangest hunting laws. In some places you can hunt, than 200 m across the field you can't.  The hunting maps in Whitchurch-Stouffville looks like a checker board!  King Twp isn't as bad
definetely looks like a 3 legged deer in the third pic. pretty interesting

Yes, unfortunately I only own a small portion of the woods and the owner of the rest won't allow us to hunt at all. But I'll bring him a case of beer and see if that changes his mind.   Roy I've been looking at that pic for a while now, magnified it and it looks like 3 legs. it was a weird pic for sure.   Sure rub it in.   Your totally right. I can hunt for cyotes in the field in front of the house but not the field 1000yrds beside it.   Interesting for sure and I can't wait to catch it again to see for sure.
Should be interesting to see whats back there Nick.
